fields.name: Local Trouble
fields.objective:
Engage Imperial Forces:
At least one Rebel ship must survive and remain in play at the end of Turn 10.
fields.bonus_1: If all Imperial ships are destroyed, all players gain 1XP.
fields.bonus_2: If no Rebel ships are destroyed, all players gain 1XP.

fields.name: Tread Softly
fields.objective:
Clear the Minefield:
Destroy minefield tokens. The mission is a success if there are fewer minefields remaining than the total number of players.
fields.bonus_1: If all minefields are destroyed, all pilots gain 2XP.
fields.bonus_2: If no replacement minefields are deployed, all pilots gain 1XP.

fields.name: Secure Holonet Receiver
fields.objective:
Configure a Secure Holo-Channel on the Receiver
1. Disable Satellite Relays and Sensor Array emplacements to identify the holonet channel used by the rebel spy.
2. The Slicer Techs must secure the identified channel.
3. The Slicer Techs must escape by jumping to hyperspace.
fields.bonus_1: The pilot who performs the most Protect actions on the Slicer Tech's HWK-290 gains 2XP. If tied, all players gain 1XP.
fields.penalty: For each Satellite Relay that is destroyed, the players lose 1XP.

fields.name: Capture the Officer
fields.objective:
Capture the Imperial Officer:
Disable the shuttle and have no other enemy ships in play.
fields.bonus_1: When the primary objective is complete, all players gain 1XP for each squad of enemy ships that did not arrive.
fields.bonus_2: The player that disables the shuttle gains 3XP.

fields.name: Nobody Home
fields.objective:
Destroy Imperial Search & Rescue Force:
If too many enemies escape, the mission is a faliure: 
1-2 players: 2 enemies
3-4 players: 3 enemies
5-6 players: 4 enemies
fields.bonus_1: If Alpha and Beta squads included any ships and they were all destroyed, all players gain 1XP.
fields.penalty: For each ship that escapes, all players lose 1XP.

fields.name: Imperial Entanglements
fields.objective:
Rescue the Transport
The transport must jump to hyperspace by the end of Turn 10, or all enemies must be destroyed.
fields.bonus_1: If the transport was not hit by Ion Pulse Missiles, all players gain 1XP.
fields.bonus_2: If the transport jumps to hyperspace AND the Decimator is destroyed, all players gain 3XP.

fields.name: R2-D2

fields.name: R3 Astromech
fields.description: You can maintain up to 2 Locks. Each must be on a different object. After you perform a Target Lock action, you may acquire a lock.

fields.name: Elusive
fields.description: While you defend, you may spend 1 Charge to reroll 1 defense die. After you execute a red maneuver, recover 1 Charge.
fields.ai_description: When defending, the attacker must reroll one Critical Hit or Hit result. You cannot use this ability if you are stressed.

Before you activate, you may flip this card.
